 networks, and multi-country frameworks 9 Develop and strengthen intersectoral and intercountry health partnerships. 10 Support and participate in ongoing migration health dialogues and cooperation across sectors and among key cities, regions, and countries of origin, transit, and destination. 11 Involve migration communities and civil society organizations as active partners, in particular for advocacy and service delivery. 177 The Right to Health Section III REFERENCES Abella, A. and Ducanes, G., 2009, \u201cThe Effect of the Global Economic Crisis on Asian Migrant Workers and Government Responses\u201d, ILO. Angsuthanasombat, K., 2008, Situation and Trends of Vietnamese Labour Export, at http://www.asianscholarship.org/asf/ejourn/ articles/kannika_a.pdf. Batistella, 2011, \u201cLabour Migration in Asia and the Role of Bilateral Migration Agreements: Market Access Facilitation by Informal Means.\u201d B\u00e9langer, D. et al., 2010, \u201cInternational Labour Migration from Viet Nam to Asian countries: Processes, Experience and Impact\u201d, report presented at the International Workshop \u2014 \u201cLabour Migration from Vietnam to Asian Countries: Sharing research findings and NGO\u2019s experiences\u201d, Hanoi, 15 March 2010. Dang, N. A., 2008, Labour Export from Vietnam: Issues of Policy and Practice, at http://apmrn.anu.edu.au/ conferences/8thAPMRNconference/10.Dang%20Anh.pdf. Herald Malaysia Online, \u201cVietnamese migrant women treated like slaves in Malaysia\u201d, 11 June 2012, at http://www. heraldmalaysia.com/news/Vietnamese-migrant-women-treated-like-slaves-in-Malaysia-11966-36-1.html. ILO/AP-Magnet, 2011, Discussion paper based on an online discussion on \u201cImproving and Regulating Recruitment Practices in Asia and the Pacific\u201d, at http://apmagnet.ilo.org/resources/resource-content/discussion-paper-ap-magnet-1/at_download/file1. IOM, 2012, \u201cInfo Sheet: The Migrant Resource Centre, Promoting Safe and Regular Labour Migration from Viet Na