uture generations in the region. The remainder of this report provides a detailed review of exactly how HIV affects individuals and households and provides estimates of the magnitude of the epidemic in the countries of the study. Using this information will provide policymakers with an effective tool to design impact mitigation strategies that are more cost-effective and HIV sensitive. 11 This analysis is based on studies undertaken by UNDP to assess the socio-economic impact of HIV at the household level in five Asian countries, Cambodia, China, India, Indonesia and Vietnam7, and additional sources of information8. In addition to using existing data from the published reports on China and India, new analyses were conducted using the data collected for Cambodia, Indonesia, and Viet Nam, as described below in Section 2.2. The country level studies were conducted over a period of six years, starting with India in 2004 and ending with Cambodia in 2010. In total, over 17,000 households were included in", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "7c84afd0-713c-4ad8-a5ad-d53b5e13f8d0": {"__data__": {"id_": "7c84afd0-713c-4ad8-a5ad-d53b5e13f8d0", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/socio-economic-impact-hiv-household-level-asia-regional-analysis", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "The Socio-Economic Impact of HIV at the Household Level in Asia: A Regional Analysis", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/socio-economic-impact-hiv-household-level-asia-regional-analysis", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "Unit