y due to the need for caregiving by household members, as discussed in the following section. FIGuRE 17 unemployment Levels 25% 26% 10% 21% 19% 14% 9% 9% 11% 3% 0% 5% 10% 15% 20% 25% 30% Cambodia China India Indonesia Viet Nam Unemployment Levels PLHIV NA-HH Members Cambodia: percentage of members 15-60 YOA not working, not performing housework, nor attending school. China: Percentage of members 18+ unemployed (not working or students \u2013 not clear if excludes housework). India: Percentage of member 18-60 YOA not working, not performing housework, nor attending school.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "0980d7e3-5b38-4d2c-a24e-4d59f2239c42": {"__data__": {"id_": "0980d7e3-5b38-4d2c-a24e-4d59f2239c42", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/socio-economic-impact-hiv-household-level-asia-regional-analysis", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "The Socio-Economic Impact of HIV at the Household Level in Asia: A Regional Analysis", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/socio-economic-impact-hiv-household-level-asia-regional-analysis", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "f76ebf8d60d696a0a0f2a7c6d7792422a10b87e093f31557c1f596dc952fe52e"}, "2": {"node_id": "bc2ce167-7675-4042-8fca-6bea6ace9752", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/socio-economic-impact-hiv-household-level-asia-regional-analysis", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Developm