ces in employment levels for males and females in the different countries, stratified by the HIV status of both the household and the household members6. In China, Indonesia, and Viet Nam, male PLHIV and non-PLHIV in HIV-HHs both had lower participation in the workforce than those in NA-HHs. In Cambodia, male PLHIV", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "ec687a8d-02ff-4045-bc4c-f1d331b485a3": {"__data__": {"id_": "ec687a8d-02ff-4045-bc4c-f1d331b485a3", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/socio-economic-impact-hiv-household-level-asia-regional-analysis-impact-women-and-girls", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "The Socio-Economic Impact of HIV at the Household Level in Asia: A Regional Analysis of the Impact on Women and Girls", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/socio-economic-impact-hiv-household-level-asia-regional-analysis-impact-women-and-girls", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "ad2cb97ad90b45d134de5a7f4f32e328bf4940c667f592d523ac1141f79cbefe"}, "3": {"node_id": "124ccbe7-c469-4b24-b67b-d52406f23e28", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/socio-economic-impact-hiv-household-level-asia-regional-analysis-impact-women-and-girls", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "b8e4cf9980b94a13428975934a9621d787eb58067190b3ae01533973266fd890"}}, "hash": "25f36707cee5ecd857b183924334ce36c0a1f5