rlier, high levels of discrimination in health facilities were reported in the Indonesia study (over 30% of PLHIV reported being discriminated against in a health facility), so it is understandable that women are hesitant to disclose their status to health professionals. While levels of PMTCT awareness in NA-HHs in Viet Nam cannot be extrapolated to those in Indonesia, it can be safely assumed that women who do not indicate they are HIV positive are considerably less likely to", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "7ecc2db1-7497-41b1-8845-c5f9e08ec381": {"__data__": {"id_": "7ecc2db1-7497-41b1-8845-c5f9e08ec381", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/socio-economic-impact-hiv-household-level-asia-regional-analysis-impact-women-and-girls", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "The Socio-Economic Impact of HIV at the Household Level in Asia: A Regional Analysis of the Impact on Women and Girls", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/socio-economic-impact-hiv-household-level-asia-regional-analysis-impact-women-and-girls", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "2403378f09552a45ce2617cc5b89c4b780c2c5928da90c72d56cfb1b6b1250e0"}, "3": {"node_id": "83ce3c89-93ab-41d7-8543-f8babc50b94f", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/socio-economic-impact-hiv-household-level-asia-regional-analysis-impact-women-and-girls", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Dev